{
  "stem": "7546.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after I came back from the Soviet Union-- or from Russia, whichever name you want to use now, now it's Russia again-- after I came back, I lived with my sister-- with my older sister because my other sister, the one that was married to Doctor Leibowicz.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, I was taken, sometimes, to work at the train station of the Lodz ghetto, to work there in unloading [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [? visas, ?] all kind of transport that came in with people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the end of 1941, I lived through something that sticks in my mind that I don't think will ever leave my-- my-- my mind.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was told to go to the train with six of my-- seven of my friends-- we're eight boys-- to unload a new transport that was coming from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were told-- and briefed, which has never happened before, briefed-- that when the luggage will come off the wagons, we should handle that luggage very carefully and put it down on the ground very carefully.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were taken, at that time, to the train station, which was in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was never a train station.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The ghetto was made into a train station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a luxury train came from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we see-- when the train stopped, we see people getting off the train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some of them were like generals.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Some of them were colonels.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The generals, you knew-- the German generals had red bands on their pants, running down from the waist line all the way down to the bottom.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were generals.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The colonels, every one of them were a high-ranking officer.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
